---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Section from '../../components/primitives/Section.astro';
import Eyebrow from '../../components/primitives/Eyebrow.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  lane="shared"
  title="Terms of service"
  description="Terms of service for S.Prestige Services — Kissonerga, Pafos, Cyprus."
>
  <Section width="narrow">
    <Eyebrow>Legal</Eyebrow>
    <h1 class="mt-3 font-display text-4xl text-fg md:text-5xl">Terms of service</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-fg-muted">Last updated: 30 April 2026</p>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-10 text-fg-muted leading-relaxed [&_h2]:font-display [&_h2]:text-xl [&_h2]:text-fg [&_h2]:mb-3 [&_h2]:mt-0 [&_h3]:font-display [&_h3]:text-base [&_h3]:text-fg [&_h3]:mt-4 [&_h3]:mb-2 [&_p]:text-sm [&_li]:text-sm [&_ul]:list-disc [&_ul]:pl-5 [&_ul]:space-y-1 [&_strong]:text-fg [&_strong]:font-medium">

      <section>
        <h2>Who we are</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>S.Prestige Services</strong> — automotive services
          business based at:
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Eustathios Plaza, Leoforos Chrisoneras, Kat.5<br/>
          Kissonerga, Pafos 8574, Cyprus
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Services these terms cover</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Detailing</strong> — hand wash, polish, ceramic coating, headlight restoration, interior + biological cleaning.</li>
          <li><strong>Mechanical service</strong> — diagnostics, servicing, brakes, suspension, pre-purchase inspections.</li>
          <li><strong>Recovery</strong> — flat-bed pickup and tow within the Pafos region, day and night.</li>
          <li><strong>Buy &amp; sell</strong> — valuations, sales and purchases of used vehicles.</li>
          <li><strong>Transfers</strong> — airport pickup and on-demand point-to-point transport.</li>
          <li><strong>Rentals</strong> — daily and weekly self-drive vehicle rentals.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          You agree to these terms when you confirm a booking — by
          WhatsApp, by phone or in person.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Quotes and pricing</h2>
        <p>
          Starting prices on this site are real and current at time of
          publishing. The firm price for your job depends on the vehicle,
          the condition and the agreed scope. We always quote a final figure
          before work begins.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          If during a job we find something material that changes the price
          (an unexpected mechanical fault, a deeper paint defect, a larger
          surface area), we stop and call you for authorisation before
          continuing. The price you confirm is the price you pay at pickup.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Payment</h2>
        <p>
          Cash and card accepted at the workshop. Bank transfer for invoiced
          jobs on request. VAT receipts available on request — S.Prestige
          Services is registered for VAT in the Republic of Cyprus.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Booking, cancellation, no-shows</h2>
        <p>
          A booking is confirmed when we send you a date and time on
          WhatsApp.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>More than 24 hours' notice</strong> — cancel or reschedule free of charge.</li>
          <li><strong>Less than 24 hours</strong> — we may charge a slot-protection fee equal to one hour of the booked work.</li>
          <li><strong>Recovery</strong> — no cancellation fee for emergency calls. We only charge once we are en route.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Service-specific terms</h2>

        <h3>Detailing and mechanical</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Drop the vehicle off with at least a quarter tank of fuel.</li>
          <li>Remove valuables and personal items beforehand. We make a reasonable effort to keep belongings safe but accept no liability for items left in the vehicle.</li>
          <li>For mechanical work we are liable for the parts and labour we install. Pre-existing faults that we did not work on remain the owner's responsibility.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Recovery</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>ETAs are real estimates based on traffic and truck location, not guaranteed times. We update you if conditions change.</li>
          <li>Drop-off is to a location you nominate (your home, our workshop, an insurer-approved garage). Out-of-region drop-off (Larnaca, Limassol, Nicosia) attracts an additional kilometre fee, quoted before pickup.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Buy &amp; sell</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Used vehicles are sold as-is. We disclose what we know in writing before sale and recommend an independent pre-purchase inspection. We perform this inspection on our own listed vehicles free of charge.</li>
          <li>For vehicles we buy from you, the WhatsApp valuation is an indicative figure based on the description and photos you send. The final price is firm only after a physical inspection.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Transfers</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Airport pickups include flight tracking and free wait time of up to 60 minutes after the scheduled landing. Beyond 60 minutes a waiting fee may apply, agreed in advance.</li>
          <li>The driver waits at arrivals with your name on a card unless you request a different meeting point.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Rentals</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Minimum age 23. Minimum two years' driving licence held.</li>
          <li>Driving licence in English or with an EU-recognised translation. International Driving Permit accepted alongside the original licence where required.</li>
          <li>A refundable deposit (typically €300–€500 depending on the vehicle) is taken at pickup. The deposit covers the standard insurance excess.</li>
          <li>Insurance is included as standard third-party cover with collision damage waiver. The renter remains liable for damage to wheels, tyres, undercarriage, windscreen and interior unless additional cover is purchased.</li>
          <li>Fuel: collect with a full tank, return with a full tank. Where the vehicle is returned short, we charge for the missing fuel at our published refuelling rate.</li>
          <li>Traffic fines and toll charges are forwarded to the renter at cost plus a €25 administrative fee per fine.</li>
          <li>Vehicles may not cross to the northern part of Cyprus (TRNC). Insurance does not extend to that territory.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Liability</h2>
        <p>
          We are responsible for damage we cause to your vehicle while in
          our care, up to the insured value. We are not responsible for:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Pre-existing wear or hidden faults we were not engaged to inspect.</li>
          <li>Delays caused by parts availability outside our reasonable control.</li>
          <li>Indirect or consequential losses (missed flights, lost work time) beyond what is recoverable under Cypriot consumer-protection law.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Nothing in these terms limits our liability for death or personal
          injury caused by our negligence, for fraud, or for anything that
          cannot be limited under Cypriot law.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Force majeure</h2>
        <p>
          Storms, fuel shortages, ferry disruption, road closures, supplier
          failure, government emergency — in any of these cases we may
          reschedule or postpone without penalty. We will tell you as soon
          as we know.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Governing law and jurisdiction</h2>
        <p>
          These terms are governed by the law of the Republic of Cyprus.
          Any dispute that cannot be resolved between us is subject to the
          exclusive jurisdiction of the Cypriot courts (Pafos District
          Court).
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Changes</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these terms as the business changes. Significant
          changes will be flagged before your next booking. The "last
          updated" date at the top reflects the current version.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          WhatsApp <a href="tel:+35796471717" class="text-gold hover:text-gold-soft">+357 96 471717</a><br/>
          In person — Eustathios Plaza, Kissonerga, Mon–Sat 08:00–18:00.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>
